head.supplied: Algae Australes ¶ ex indice ¶ Harveyi ¶ [Southern Algae from Harvey's list] ¶ 1855....

div.p: C41.2, Library, Royal Botanic Gardens Melbourne.

During his visit to Melbourne in 1855, William Harvey sorted M's algal collections (see M to W. Hooker, 26 April 1855).This list is a copy by M of part of Harvey's MS 'Systematic list of Australian Algae 1854 —' (MS, Herbarium, Trinity College, Dublin), in which Harvey listed his 'Travelling Set' specimens, arranged in systematic order. The copy made by M includes Phaeophyta (brown algae) and part of Rhodophyta (red algae), but not Chlorophyta (green algae), fromHarvey's list. Harvey gave M a set of duplicates (where available) from his Victorian 'Travelling Set' collections. In the Travelling Set the species were numbered chronologically in order of first collecting. The underlined names seem to indicate species collected by M; others are marked 'x', and appear to indicate species of which M received a duplicate from Harvey (gift of specimens acknowledged in M to W. Haines, 25 June 1855).
Since the list has some annotations by Harvey, it must have been written by M between 26 April and 5 May 1855, the only time when M and Harvey were both in Melbourne after Harvey had completed his Victorian collections and before he finally left Melbourne bound for Sydney.
The list of algae published by M in B55.11.01, which he says he ‘enumerated chiefly from the collections and from the notes of Professor Harvey’, uses a different systematic arrangement than that used by Harvey and in the present list, and does not include many of the 'Travelling Set' specimens M received from Harvey and listed here.

cell.p:
[496 MEL]
This column lists Harvey's 'Travelling Set' numbers in square brackets. They do not appear in the MS, but are taken from Harvey's Dublin MS. 'MEL' indicates that a Harvey duplicate specimen is in the collections of the National Herbarium of Victoria.

cell.style: border: none; padding-top: 0in; padding-left: 0.0555in; padding-bottom: 0in; padding-right: 0.0555in;
cell.p:
Pt Ph
M's locality abbreviations are: 'Bright' = Brighton; 'Geel' = Geelong; 'Ph isl' = Phillip Island; 'Pt F' or 'Pt Fair' = Port Fairy; 'Pt Lons' = Point Lonsdale; 'Pt Ph' = Port Phillip; 'W Pt' = Western Port; Willt. = Williamstown. All these localities are in Victoria. Harvey gave no localities on his list now in Dublin.
